Given the complex presentation of immunodeficiency, recurrent infections, autoimmune symptoms, and multisystem involvement, the following differential diagnoses are considered:

1. Common Variable Immunodeficiency (CVID)
2. Chronic Granulomatous Disease
3. Hyper IgM Syndrome
4. Wiskott-Aldrich Syndrome
5. Autoimmune Lymphoproliferative Syndrome (ALPS)
6. Severe Combined Immunodeficiency (SCID)
7. Ataxia-Telangiectasia
8. DiGeorge Syndrome
9. Hyper IgA Syndrome
10. Leukocyte Adhesion Deficiency